<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1519,1905]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1519,1545]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This new genus is defined by the following combination of characters: postpedicel with broad base, with apical half tapered; stylus comprises two articles, shorter or longer than half length of postpedicel with apical mechanoreceptor or sensillum greatly reduced in length; prosternum isolated, not fused to proepisternum; scutellum with 2–3 pairs of apical setae; laterotergite bare; male hind femur usually modified; wing with basal costal seta present; R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[268,294,1681,1695]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">4+5</subScript>
branched or unbranched; cell dm produced apically (
<figureCitation box="[916,1002,1663,1689]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–10" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1171,1195]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1147]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[151,1435,181,1147]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 8–10. Species of Paraiteaphila and Iteaphila with unbranched R 4+5, lateral view. 8, I. longipalpis, male, scale bar = 1 mm; 9, I. parastentor, male, scale bar = 0.5 mm; 10, Paraiteaphila sp., female, scale bar = 0.75 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4745574" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4745574/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
); male terminalia with epandrial lobe ventral to distinctly digitiform surstylus; phallic guide and inner apodeme absent (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Shamshev, I. V. &amp; Sinclair, B. J." box="[1116,1436,1699,1725]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="441 - 450" refId="ref85119" refString="Shamshev, I. V. &amp; Sinclair, B. J. (2009) Revision of the Iteaphila setosa group (Diptera: Empididae). European Journal of Entomology, 106, 441 - 450. https: // doi. org / 10.14411 / eje. 2009.055" type="journal article" year="2009">Shamshev &amp; Sinclair (2009)</bibRefCitation>
for further details).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
